# PersonalDealIntelligence rules

- Keep the initial build scoped to the Banking MVP.
- Do not add clothing, travel, flights, hotels, cashback stack optimization, browser extensions, or automated financial actions unless a future issue explicitly changes scope.
- Do not add live source collection without explicit machine-readable source policy and disabled-by-default validation.
- Do not add source-access workarounds, private-session collection, credentials, private auth material, private customer data, or highly sensitive personal identifiers.
- Keep tests offline by default.
- Preserve evidence for extracted banking terms.
- Mark ambiguous or missing banking terms as unknown rather than guessing.
